  'Part II', 'Physics MCQs', 'NSTC',
  2023, 'NSTC 2023 Physics Paper', 'The force required to start an object sliding across a uniform horizontal surface is larger than the force required to keep the object sliding at a constant velocity. The magnitudes of the required forces are different in these situations because the force of kinetic friction',
  '["Is greater than the force of static friction","Is less than the force of static friction","Increases as the speed of the object relative to the surface increases","Decreases as the speed of the object relative to the surface increases"]'::jsonb, 1, 'Static friction is generally greater than kinetic friction because when two surfaces are at rest relative to each other, the microscopic bumps and imperfections on their surfaces can interlock more completely. This interlocking, along with electromagnetic interactions at the contact points, requires more force to overcome. Once the object starts moving, the surfaces don’t have time to fully interlock at each point of contact, so the interactions are less strong. As a result, kinetic friction is typically lower.',
  5, '', '{}'::jsonb
